'''Malaysia League XI''' (also known as''' Malaysia XI''', '''Malaysia Selection''', or '''Malaysia League Selection''') is a football team which represents [[Malaysia]] to participate in exhibitional matches. Malaysia XI mainly play Non FIFA 'A' international match while the competitive matches such as [[FIFA World Cup qualification|World Cup Qualifiers]] and the [[AFC Asian Cup|Asian Cup]] are played by the [[Malaysia national football team]].
==History== The team is formed by the top players in the [[Super League Malaysia|Malaysian League]]. Some of the players are mainly from the [[Malaysia national football team|Malaysia national team]]. Malaysia XI usually plays against [[Association football|Associated Football clubs]] throughout the world mostly from [[England]].
In recent years, [[Football Association of Malaysia|FAM]] has always arranged matches between the Malaysian side and clubs throughout the world. Malaysia XI doesn't play a match for a few years. They only play a match if they are invited to. The team mainly play against a pre season friendly match for the opposite team to be prepared for their leagues.
Malaysia XI is usually coached by the [[Malaysia national football team|Malaysia national team]]. The team coach is currently [[K. Rajagopal]]. Malaysia XI only recorded one win and three draws since their match at 1974.
Malaysia XI will play the visiting English team, [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]], and [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] on July 2011.
